data.text:
Siekiera were a Polish coldwave/art-punk band from Puławy, formed in 1983 and initially active for five years. In 1986, the band released a standalone single and the album Nowa Aleksandria on Tonpress. A clutch of 1984-era demos and live recordings were collected on two CDs released by W Moich Oczach in the late 2000s.

Members:

Tomasz Adamski (guitar, vocals), Tomasz Budzyński (vocals, 1983-84), Jerzy Janaczek (bass, 1983), Irek Czerniak (drums, 1983), Dariusz Malinowski (bass, vocals, 1983-88), Krzysztof Grela (drums, 1983-84), Piotr Szewczyk (guitar, 1984), Paweł Młynarczyk (keyboards, 1985-88), Zbigniew Musiński (drums, 1985-88), Wiesław Borysewicz (guitar, 1987-88) Discography:
